<h1 id="harvest-or-add-data">Harvest or add data</h1>
<p>You can publish datasets to the data.gov.uk directory by:</p>

<ul>
<li>using software to <a href="harvest_data/#harvest-data">harvest datasets</a></li>
<li><a href="add_data/#add-data-manually">adding datasets manually</a></li>
</ul>
<p>Harvesting means using software, known as a ‘harvester’, to collect datasets from your website and publish them on the data.gov.uk directory. Using the harvester lets you publish more than one dataset at once. You can also schedule harvests.</p>

<blockquote>
<p>You must harvest <a href="inspire/#inspire">Location/INSPIRE data</a>.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>If you’d like to showcase your data by making it part of the new <a href="https://data.gov.uk">curated data collections</a>, you can express your interest through our <a href="https://forms.office.com/e/9V26PNFQaR">feedback form</a>.</p>
